    {
      "id": "typography-contract-problem",
      "type": "section",
      "label": "Problem",
      "root": false,
      "position": {
        "x": -430,
        "y": 120
      },
      "width": 520,
      "height": 320,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "title": "Problem Statement",
        "summary": "Twilite currently has color themes, but not a typography system. Many node classes and editor surfaces choose font size, weight, family, and spacing locally. The result is legible but not governed, and quality depends too much on one-off styling decisions.",
        "level": "h2",
        "anchor": "problem-statement",
        "status": "active",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "section",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/document-publishing/section.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/document-publishing/section.node-class.node"
        },
        "_bridge": {
          "sourceNodeId": "typography-contract-bridge-section",
          "sourceBridgeNodeId": "typography-contract-bridge-section",
          "sourceBridgeLabel": "Section",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/document-publishing/section.node-class.node",
          "entryPort": "root",
          "kind": "node-class",
          "targetKind": "node-class",
          "classKey": "section",
          "classRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/document-publishing/section.node-class.node"
        },
        "definitionKey": "section"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "typography-contract-roles",
      "type": "section",
      "label": "Roles",
      "root": false,
      "position": {
        "x": 150,
        "y": 120
      },
      "width": 520,
      "height": 340,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "title": "Core Type Roles",
        "summary": "The system should define a small set of shared roles: display, title, body, label, meta, and mono. Display handles strong document and landing statements. Title handles card and section headers. Body handles readable prose. Label and meta handle UI chrome and status language. Mono is reserved for code, ids, and machine-facing output.",
        "level": "h2",
        "anchor": "core-type-roles",
        "status": "active",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "section",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/document-publishing/section.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/document-publishing/section.node-class.node"
        },
        "_bridge": {
          "sourceNodeId": "typography-contract-bridge-section",
          "sourceBridgeNodeId": "typography-contract-bridge-section",
          "sourceBridgeLabel": "Section",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/document-publishing/section.node-class.node",
          "entryPort": "root",
          "kind": "node-class",
          "targetKind": "node-class",
          "classKey": "section",
          "classRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/document-publishing/section.node-class.node"
        },
        "definitionKey": "section"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "typography-contract-rules",
      "type": "section",
      "label": "Rules",
      "root": false,
      "position": {
        "x": 730,
        "y": 120
      },
      "width": 560,
      "height": 360,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "title": "System Rules",
        "summary": "Typography decisions should live in the theme and shared tokens first, not in arbitrary local styles. Browser theme and graph theme are separate authorities built from the same token contract: browser chrome governs the ambient application shell, while a graph theme overrides only when the graph explicitly provides one. If a graph does not expose a theme node or equivalent theme config, it inherits the browser theme by default. Local overrides are acceptable only when the surface has a clear semantic reason. Browser chrome, task/document nodes, reference surfaces, and edge labels should all read from the same role vocabulary before specialty nodes are tuned individually.",
        "level": "h2",
        "anchor": "system-rules",
        "status": "active",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "section",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/document-publishing/section.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/document-publishing/section.node-class.node"
        },
        "_bridge": {
          "sourceNodeId": "typography-contract-bridge-section",
          "sourceBridgeNodeId": "typography-contract-bridge-section",
          "sourceBridgeLabel": "Section",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/document-publishing/section.node-class.node",
          "entryPort": "root",
          "kind": "node-class",
          "targetKind": "node-class",
          "classKey": "section",
          "classRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/document-publishing/section.node-class.node"
        },
        "definitionKey": "section"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "typography-contract-adoption",
      "type": "section",
      "label": "Adoption",
      "root": false,
      "position": {
        "x": 1310,
        "y": 120
      },
      "width": 560,
      "height": 360,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "title": "Adoption Order",
        "summary": "Adopt the system in layers. First define shared typography tokens and family strategy. Then compose those tokens into two explicit MUI theme scopes: browser theme for application chrome and graph theme for authored content. A graph theme should only apply when the graph exposes one; otherwise the graph falls back to the browser theme. After that, apply the shared roles to browser/editor chrome, task and summary surfaces, reference surfaces, and edge labels. Only after the shared surfaces are stable should specialty utility nodes receive their own tuned exceptions.",
        "level": "h2",
        "anchor": "adoption-order",
        "status": "active",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "section",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/document-publishing/section.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/document-publishing/section.node-class.node"
        },
        "_bridge": {
          "sourceNodeId": "typography-contract-bridge-section",
          "sourceBridgeNodeId": "typography-contract-bridge-section",
          "sourceBridgeLabel": "Section",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/document-publishing/section.node-class.node",
          "entryPort": "root",
          "kind": "node-class",
          "targetKind": "node-class",
          "classKey": "section",
          "classRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/document-publishing/section.node-class.node"
        },
        "definitionKey": "section"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "typography-contract-summary",
      "type": "document-summary",
      "label": "Summary",
      "root": false,
      "position": {
        "x": -1110,
        "y": 470
      },
      "width": 420,
      "height": 260,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "title": "Summary",
        "summary": "Twilite needs a typography contract, not just fonts. The system should define shared roles, move primary decisions into theme-level tokens, keep browser theme and graph theme as separate authorities on the same contract, let graphs fall back to the browser theme when they do not expose their own theme, and adopt the shared language across browser chrome and common node surfaces before tuning specialty nodes.",
        "scope": "Typography system",
        "audience": "Reader",
        "status": "active",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "document-summary",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/document-publishing/document-summary.node-class.node"
        },
        "_bridge": {
          "sourceBridgeNodeId": "typography-contract-bridge-summary",
          "sourceBridgeLabel": "Summary",
          "targetKind": "node-class",
          "classKey": "document-summary",
          "classRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/library/classes/nodes/document-publishing/document-summary.node-class.node"
        },
        "definitionKey": "document-summary"
      }
    },
